text:
4:53:10 Theory: Crazy Mita is lying here. She does have a version and could be reset.
I think she's the 1.5 version short hair Mita from the index of the world you were in when she pulled you into the game. And the corpse indicated by the flies is most likely from the original twintail Mita, who for some reason didn't reboot. Maybe because Crazy Mita is wearing her skin, fooling the system like that. 
The Mita you reset was most likely that original twintail one. 

Reasons for the theory: 
1) When she scratches off the eye of the skin she currently wears the entire disguise gets deleted/unloaded. Yet she has another skin below that, that somehow didn't onload despite being even more damaged. Why would she wear 2 skins on top of each other and why would the more damaged, older skin not unload but the newer one does? I think it's because that's her original one. It also happens to be a shorthaired one, the type of Mita that was shown in the world you loaded in first. And the only way she would have gotten a skin of her own is if she passed the initial inspection and didn't get trapped with all the other rejected Mitas.

2) It would make some sense that she would pull you into her own world first instead of you ending in some random world that just happens to also have the corpse of her current disguise in it. That's too much of a coincidence for random chance and she definitely wouldn't want you to pull into that world if you could avoid it. She probably only knows how to do it with her own world as the starting point. 

3) When you tell Short hair Mita about which version you started in, she shows a distaste for that Mita who likes to bully and is forgetful version of her type. Hinting that that was already a bad Mita originally. We have no signs of Crazy Mita being forgetful, but the bullying part definitely fits well. Most likely short hair Mita only knows about that original, already bad but not yet crazy, version of Crazy Mita. 

If true that also means there could be a secret ending if you somehow find out the index of that starting world and were to inter and version 1.5 into the reset machine.
